      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which directly maps to the clinical endpoint (patient hemolysis risk). Secondary QoI includes pump pressure head (surrogate for device performance) and wall shear stress distribution (mechanistic link to red blood cell damage). All QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision: identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
