    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error (iterative convergence and round-off) is scoped out at MRL 2 for this assessment because the commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) provides robust residual monitoring and the simulation protocol specifies convergence criteria of 1×10⁻⁶ for all residuals. Solver round-off error is negligible relative to discretization uncertainty (GCI 4.7%) and is not a credibility-limiting factor at this model risk level. Iterative convergence documented in simulation logs archived with the package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out at MRL 2 because the simulation workflow is executed by a single qualified analyst under a documented simulation protocol (SP-CFD-CPB-2023-01) with independent technical review of boundary conditions, mesh, and post-processing steps. The protocol includes mandatory peer review checklists. Formal use-error FMEA is reserved for MRL 3 and above per organizational credibility policy CP-2023-03."
