    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, non-Newtonian blood rheology representation) is scoped out at MRL 2. Turbulence model sensitivity was qualitatively assessed during validation (k-ω SST vs. realizable k-ε, maximum 14% WSS difference noted). Full model form uncertainty quantification via multi-model ensemble is reserved for MRL 3. The adopted k-ω SST model is the consensus recommendation in the FDA CFD hemolysis guidance document."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model input uncertainty (geometric tolerances, fluid property variability, boundary condition uncertainty) is scoped out at MRL 2. A qualitative sensitivity study was performed varying inlet flow rate ±5% and rotational speed ±2%; NIH sensitivity was low (±8% NIH change). Full probabilistic input uncertainty propagation is reserved for MRL 3 assessments per credibility policy CP-2023-03."
